9
00:00:49,525 --> 00:00:53,614
Sorry, my car broke down. So we need to walk.

10
00:00:53,763 --> 00:00:54,671
We’re almost there.

11
00:00:56,579 --> 00:01:00,000
You said that 20 minutes ago.

12
00:01:00,130 --> 00:01:02,130
(That was what I wanted to do.)

13
00:01:02,130 --> 00:01:04,846
(But without knowing it, the one next to me was gone.)

14
00:01:04,846 --> 00:01:05,973
Where are my friends?

15
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:07,014
Right here.

16
00:01:09,133 --> 00:01:10,720
Why are they crowing?

17
00:01:10,885 --> 00:01:12,646
This hill is freaking steep.

18
00:01:12,961 --> 00:01:16,125
Why is your dad doing this to us?

19
00:01:16,125 --> 00:01:17,940
I think we should head back.

20
00:01:19,052 --> 00:01:20,254
You still want to walk?

21
00:01:21,052 --> 00:01:22,298
You out of your mind?

22
00:01:22,298 --> 00:01:24,402
It’d be dark until we get down there.

23
00:01:24,402 --> 00:01:25,865
What if there’s a bear?

24
00:01:26,394 --> 00:01:27,840
There’s no bear on this mountain.

25
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:30,319
There’s no bear here. There’re only pigs.

26
00:01:31,195 --> 00:01:32,377
What kind of pig?

27
00:01:32,377 --> 00:01:33,672
Those that give us Kurobuta?

28
00:01:33,806 --> 00:01:34,762
Wild boars.

29
00:01:34,943 --> 00:01:37,420
They attacked the villagers the other day, spilling out their guts.

30
00:01:37,420 --> 00:01:38,163
Shit!

31
00:01:38,822 --> 00:01:41,389
Fah, call your dad.

32
00:01:41,389 --> 00:01:42,445
Tell him to send someone to take us home.

33
00:01:42,445 --> 00:01:46,624
If I could really do that, we wouldn’t be here, would we?

34
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:48,153
Come on. Let’s go.

35
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:50,283
Help me up.

36
00:01:51,552 --> 00:01:52,290
Come on.

37
00:01:52,290 --> 00:01:54,149
Hey! Slowly.

38
00:01:58,082 --> 00:02:01,395
After that, any mountains were the same to me.

39
00:02:02,162 --> 00:02:04,162
Without someone walking alongside me,

40
00:02:04,302 --> 00:02:06,541
I didn’t see the point of climbing mountains anymore.

41
00:02:09,201 --> 00:02:11,760
Big bro, where are you from?

42
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,419
You are so handsome.

43
00:02:13,419 --> 00:02:15,457
Come here. Look!

44
00:02:17,963 --> 00:02:20,053
Mister, are you an actor?

45
00:02:20,053 --> 00:02:22,194
Children, don’t bother him.

46
00:02:22,194 --> 00:02:23,372
Back off a little.

47
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,591
But then I realized that maybe…

48
00:02:36,591 --> 00:02:41,308
we climb a mountain just to meet someone waiting for us up there.

49
00:03:49,935 --> 00:03:51,368
Come on, children.

50
00:03:52,029 --> 00:03:53,432
Let’s get back inside.

51
00:04:09,078 --> 00:04:09,988
Fah.

52
00:04:10,839 --> 00:04:12,138
What are you dreaming about?

53
00:04:12,138 --> 00:04:12,991
Keep walking.

54
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:18,493
People from Bangkok might find it hard to live here.

55
00:04:18,790 --> 00:04:20,790
We don’t have electricity.

56
00:04:21,036 --> 00:04:23,753
We only have solar power that barely works.

57
00:04:24,127 --> 00:04:26,127
The phone reception is very poor as well.

58
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,255
Poor phone reception?

59
00:04:28,255 --> 00:04:28,949
Yes.

60
00:04:29,858 --> 00:04:31,500
That’s another necessity of life.

61
00:04:33,108 --> 00:04:37,107
Then what do you have up here?

62
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,180
This.

63
00:04:38,499 --> 00:04:39,723
Do you want some?

64
00:04:41,498 --> 00:04:43,170
Very tempting but

65
00:04:44,408 --> 00:04:45,466
no thanks.

66
00:04:45,884 --> 00:04:47,099
Uncle,

67
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:49,683
we traveled all the way to Chiang Mai's hilltop

68
00:04:49,683 --> 00:04:52,306
in the hopes of finding a nice BBQ and a great view.

69
00:04:52,490 --> 00:04:53,800
What do you even have here?

70
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,686
Karaoke?

71
00:04:54,686 --> 00:04:55,566
And Bingsoo?

72
00:04:55,566 --> 00:04:57,059
Bingsoo, seriously?

73
00:04:57,059 --> 00:04:58,151
Let’s just go.

74
00:04:58,686 --> 00:05:00,000
He’s done with you two.

75
00:05:00,784 --> 00:05:01,949
Uncle.

76
00:05:07,937 --> 00:05:09,937
What are we doing here?

77
00:05:11,087 --> 00:05:13,280
This is Dr. Fah’s accommodation.

78
00:05:13,374 --> 00:05:15,120
You two share a house.

79
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:15,927
What?

80
00:05:16,947 --> 00:05:19,200
Why does he get a private house?

81
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,544
Right.

82
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:23,040
Tell me how much he paid you.

83
00:05:23,234 --> 00:05:26,129
I’ll give you more.

84
00:05:26,129 --> 00:05:28,062
Uncle, can we have another private house?

85
00:05:28,062 --> 00:05:29,147
You guys

86
00:05:29,608 --> 00:05:30,862
stop bothering him.

87
00:05:31,471 --> 00:05:33,471
I happen to be so handsome.

88
00:05:33,471 --> 00:05:35,134
That’s why I get a VIP house.

89
00:05:35,545 --> 00:05:36,720
Wait a minute.

90
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,797
That’s your reason? Handsome?

91
00:05:38,797 --> 00:05:39,878
Being handsome gets you a house?

92
00:05:39,878 --> 00:05:42,738
I’m a doctor. That’s why.

93
00:05:42,738 --> 00:05:43,933
That’s all.

94
00:05:44,405 --> 00:05:45,441
So?

95
00:05:45,441 --> 00:05:46,405
What about us?

96
00:05:47,281 --> 00:05:48,157
No.

97
00:05:48,157 --> 00:05:50,963
I meant I’m a doctor. I need to work and rest.

98
00:05:50,963 --> 00:05:51,849
What?

99
00:05:51,849 --> 00:05:52,789
And I don’t need to rest?

100
00:05:52,789 --> 00:05:53,914
I don’t need to work?

101
00:05:53,914 --> 00:05:56,021
You two can share a house.

102
00:05:56,021 --> 00:05:57,568
I don’t want to share a house with him. He snores.

103
00:05:57,568 --> 00:06:00,635
- You snore too.
- You’re louder.

104
00:06:00,843 --> 00:06:03,022
Let’s go, Uncle.

105
00:06:10,153 --> 00:06:12,153
No one has lived in this house for a long time.

106
00:06:12,153 --> 00:06:13,088
You need to clean it a bit.

107
00:06:15,443 --> 00:06:18,000
Wow! VIP indeed.

108
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,800
The house that comes with cobwebs.

109
00:06:20,949 --> 00:06:21,952
Awesome!

110
00:06:21,952 --> 00:06:23,655
A luxurious house in the heart of the mountains.

111
00:06:23,655 --> 00:06:26,888
You wake up to a sea of mist and the unpaved road.

112
00:06:26,888 --> 00:06:27,797
Wow!

113
00:06:27,797 --> 00:06:29,826
A great location you can’t find anywhere.

114
00:06:30,423 --> 00:06:32,125
Good luck. You’ll love it here.

115
00:06:33,010 --> 00:06:34,413
I didn’t think it’d be this bad.

116
00:06:34,413 --> 00:06:36,443
Uncle, where is our house?

117
00:06:36,443 --> 00:06:37,450
That way.

118
00:06:38,353 --> 00:06:39,565
Please give us a nice one.

119
00:06:39,565 --> 00:06:40,353
Sure.

120
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,280
Hold on.

121
00:06:42,281 --> 00:06:44,281
Keep me company.

122
00:06:44,634 --> 00:06:46,634
Wasn’t it you who wanted to be alone?

123
00:06:46,634 --> 00:06:47,711
The VIP man.

124
00:06:47,711 --> 00:06:49,711
Help me clean up, at least.

125
00:06:50,024 --> 00:06:53,605
I won’t dare step into a doctor’s house.

126
00:06:53,605 --> 00:06:54,789
We don’t want to bother.

127
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,749
You have it all to yourself. It’s a house for one.

128
00:06:57,167 --> 00:06:57,989
See you.

129
00:06:57,989 --> 00:06:59,167
Hang in there, man.

130
00:06:59,167 --> 00:07:00,582
Clean up nicely, VIP man.

131
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,255
So many yantra amulets.

132
00:07:20,411 --> 00:07:22,083
Why are there so many yantra amulets?

133
00:07:47,025 --> 00:07:47,960
Children.

134
00:07:48,258 --> 00:07:50,920
Guys, I’m here.

135
00:07:51,466 --> 00:07:52,750
Wanna play games?

136
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:54,496
Let’s go.

137
00:07:57,424 --> 00:07:59,920
Wee-ah, it’s my turn. You sweep the floor.

138
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,688
Two more games.

139
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:04,360
Teacher Prince is coming.

140
00:08:13,909 --> 00:08:14,800
Shh!

141
00:08:19,789 --> 00:08:21,043
Where are the children?

142
00:08:21,043 --> 00:08:22,356
So you speak the central dialect too?

143
00:08:22,819 --> 00:08:24,400
I asked you where the children were.

144
00:08:25,235 --> 00:08:26,354
Children?

145
00:08:28,031 --> 00:08:29,119
What children?

146
00:08:29,626 --> 00:08:30,760
It’s just me here.

147
00:08:37,712 --> 00:08:40,816
Tell me why you’re skipping class.

148
00:08:40,816 --> 00:08:44,567
This man threatened to hit us if we didn’t help him clean up.

149
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:45,341
What?

150
00:08:45,561 --> 00:08:46,964
Who threatened you?

151
00:08:49,392 --> 00:08:51,080
We will talk again in school.

152
00:08:51,257 --> 00:08:54,630
I’ll see you guys there in one minute.

153
00:08:55,495 --> 00:08:56,405
Go.

154
00:09:07,530 --> 00:09:08,720
As for you,

155
00:09:09,127 --> 00:09:10,679
did you really threaten them?

156
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:13,478
I didn’t.

157
00:09:13,612 --> 00:09:17,851
I just asked them to help me clean up in exchange for some mobile games.

158
00:09:18,041 --> 00:09:20,640
Didn’t you know they had class?

159
00:09:21,311 --> 00:09:23,102
How would I know that?

160
00:09:23,281 --> 00:09:24,669
I just got here.

161
00:09:26,298 --> 00:09:28,298
Next time, stay clear of my students.

162
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:33,433
You’re a volunteer doctor, you should know…

163
00:09:35,223 --> 00:09:36,318
Hey!

164
00:09:38,164 --> 00:09:41,280
It’s rude not to give eye contact during a conversation.

165
00:09:41,549 --> 00:09:44,444
But on your head,

166
00:09:46,306 --> 00:09:47,680
there’s a spider.

167
00:10:24,939 --> 00:10:26,133
Come on.

168
00:10:26,765 --> 00:10:29,571
If you’re scared, why didn’t you say anything?

169
00:10:29,869 --> 00:10:30,960
Why acted cool?

170
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:31,830
None of your business.

171
00:10:32,447 --> 00:10:34,447
Don't mess with my students again.

172
00:10:34,596 --> 00:10:36,000
I’m warning you.

173
00:10:52,391 --> 00:10:54,570
Time for me to go.

174
00:10:56,086 --> 00:10:58,981
You got all the essential medicines?

175
00:10:59,667 --> 00:11:00,658
I do.

176
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:04,589
And the food in the fridge,

177
00:11:05,439 --> 00:11:06,842
do you have enough?

178
00:11:07,021 --> 00:11:08,202
I do.

179
00:11:08,381 --> 00:11:09,539
Hold on.

180
00:11:09,758 --> 00:11:11,848
I should be the one checking on you.

181
00:11:12,237 --> 00:11:14,893
Make sure you have everything. You’re about to hit the road.

182
00:11:15,641 --> 00:11:17,641
Well, I’m worried about you.

183
00:11:18,647 --> 00:11:20,280
Don’t worry about me.

184
00:11:20,572 --> 00:11:23,258
I have Khabkluen to take care of me here.

185
00:11:25,288 --> 00:11:28,123
I’m worried because you’re with him.

186
00:11:31,192 --> 00:11:32,595
While I’m away,

187
00:11:33,699 --> 00:11:35,639
take good care of my brother.

188
00:11:35,943 --> 00:11:39,200
Don’t do anything bad to him.

189
00:11:41,084 --> 00:11:43,084
What do you consider bad?

190
00:11:44,813 --> 00:11:46,160
You know what I mean.

191
00:11:47,206 --> 00:11:50,400
Is holding hands allowed?

192
00:11:52,618 --> 00:11:53,760
It is.

193
00:11:54,001 --> 00:11:55,720
And kissing on the cheek?

194
00:11:59,515 --> 00:12:00,978
Twice a day is fine.

195
00:12:06,978 --> 00:12:08,978
I’ve reached my quota.

196
00:12:11,108 --> 00:12:12,640
Kissing on the lips?

197
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,217
Kiss my foot!

198
00:12:14,582 --> 00:12:17,040
I’m being nice to you and now you want to cross me?

199
00:12:17,492 --> 00:12:18,955
I’m kidding.

200
00:12:18,955 --> 00:12:21,664
I promise to take very good care of Dao.

201
00:12:21,664 --> 00:12:23,076
I will do anything bad.

202
00:12:25,637 --> 00:12:28,520
I will not do anything bad.

203
00:12:29,564 --> 00:12:30,626
Okay.

204
00:12:31,231 --> 00:12:34,000
Don’t worry about me. Worry about yourself.

205
00:12:34,595 --> 00:12:36,595
Take good care of yourself while you’re there.

206
00:12:37,608 --> 00:12:41,368
Consider it your personal time.

207
00:12:44,083 --> 00:12:45,190
Yeah.

208
00:12:47,008 --> 00:12:48,240
Take care.

209
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,960
Have a safe trip, Fah.

210
00:13:02,555 --> 00:13:03,543
Dao,

211
00:13:05,095 --> 00:13:07,360
can I go beyond my quota?

212
00:13:08,771 --> 00:13:10,019
No.

213
00:13:10,019 --> 00:13:11,010
Why not?

214
00:13:12,397 --> 00:13:15,978
You’ve met all your quota for today.

215
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,171
But…

216
00:13:19,931 --> 00:13:21,440
I haven’t.

217
00:13:27,618 --> 00:13:28,421
Come on.

218
00:13:29,256 --> 00:13:30,560
There’s still some quota left.

219
00:13:36,185 --> 00:13:36,965
Hey.

220
00:13:37,562 --> 00:13:38,931
What are you daydreaming about?

221
00:13:39,265 --> 00:13:40,937
Thinking of girls in Bangkok?

222
00:13:41,101 --> 00:13:42,000
Like I have any.

223
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:44,966
I haven’t yelled at you for ditching me yet.

224
00:13:45,521 --> 00:13:46,835
We didn’t ditch you.

225
00:13:47,059 --> 00:13:49,059
We just went with the flow.

226
00:13:49,059 --> 00:13:50,325
Yeah. Whatever.

227
00:13:50,508 --> 00:13:52,747
I’m done with your excuses.

228
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:55,080
I’m hungry. Let’s find something to eat.

229
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,175
Perfect timing.

230
00:13:56,175 --> 00:13:58,571
The village chief invited us for dinner at his house.

231
00:13:58,571 --> 00:13:59,481
Let’s go.

232
00:14:04,046 --> 00:14:05,640
I told you to wash your face.

233
00:14:07,544 --> 00:14:09,544
You’re just 25 and already a doctor?
[VILLAGE CHIEF OFFICE]

234
00:14:09,544 --> 00:14:11,302
He’s a genius.

235
00:14:11,709 --> 00:14:13,280
He got a high school equivalency certificate at 16.

236
00:14:13,843 --> 00:14:15,843
Took a test for med school after that.

237
00:14:15,843 --> 00:14:16,562
And he got accepted.

238
00:14:16,562 --> 00:14:18,052
You’re great.

239
00:14:18,230 --> 00:14:20,720
I bet many hospitals fight over you.

240
00:14:20,876 --> 00:14:22,279
Fight over him?

241
00:14:22,348 --> 00:14:25,243
All he does is drink in a bar.

242
00:14:25,243 --> 00:14:26,308
Stop talking already.

243
00:14:26,308 --> 00:14:28,036
You may call him a bad doctor.

244
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,111
Hello.

245
00:14:32,111 --> 00:14:32,773
Hi.

246
00:14:32,773 --> 00:14:33,680
Have a seat.

247
00:14:33,949 --> 00:14:34,925
Sit here.

248
00:14:39,431 --> 00:14:40,506
Your son?

249
00:14:40,792 --> 00:14:42,673
No, he’s not.

250
00:14:42,673 --> 00:14:46,769
This is Teacher Prince, the other volunteer teacher here.

251
00:14:46,769 --> 00:14:50,313
I invited him over since you all need to work together.

252
00:14:51,229 --> 00:14:53,020
So you’re a volunteer teacher?

253
00:14:53,339 --> 00:14:55,100
I’m a volunteer teacher too.

254
00:14:55,130 --> 00:14:57,578
My name is Mesa. Nice to meet you.

255
00:14:59,509 --> 00:15:01,509
Of course. I’m Prince.

256
00:15:01,749 --> 00:15:04,256
Mesa, a person’s name, not a month (April).

257
00:15:06,936 --> 00:15:08,339
I’m JJ.

258
00:15:08,339 --> 00:15:09,598
A Maintenance Officer.

259
00:15:09,789 --> 00:15:11,789
What a nice title.

260
00:15:11,940 --> 00:15:13,940
All you will do is fix houses and paint.

261
00:15:14,716 --> 00:15:15,594
Asshole.

262
00:15:16,448 --> 00:15:17,583
Sorry.

263
00:15:18,112 --> 00:15:20,560
And this foul-mouthed man is Kuafah.

264
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:21,083
He’s a …

265
00:15:21,083 --> 00:15:22,353
A burden, isn’t he?

266
00:15:27,056 --> 00:15:28,429
You two have met?

267
00:15:29,864 --> 00:15:32,610
We met while I was cleaning up the house.

268
00:15:33,087 --> 00:15:34,093
Never mind.

269
00:15:34,342 --> 00:15:35,521
Long story.

270
00:15:35,670 --> 00:15:37,297
Let’s eat.

271
00:15:37,844 --> 00:15:39,635
All right. We should eat now.

272
00:15:39,635 --> 00:15:40,554
Make yourself at home.

273
00:15:41,529 --> 00:15:42,813
Can you please pass me those plates?

274
00:15:45,506 --> 00:15:46,581
Let me help.

275
00:15:49,041 --> 00:15:51,220
I’m helping.

276
00:15:51,712 --> 00:15:54,000
Please enjoy. Eat as much as you want.

277
00:16:08,885 --> 00:16:11,482
Mom made extra food for the guests.

278
00:16:11,482 --> 00:16:12,528
Put them right here.

279
00:16:37,826 --> 00:16:40,423
This is Yayah, my daughter.

