I see that you don’t call Kuafah Phi either.

565
00:33:21,044 --> 00:33:23,380
So I wasn’t sure how to talk to you.

566
00:33:24,675 --> 00:33:28,210
‘Phi’ is only for those I respect.

567
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:32,492
I’m sorry about him.

568
00:33:32,947 --> 00:33:35,812
I know this might not help

569
00:33:36,100 --> 00:33:40,304
but he’s being like that because he’s heartbroken.

570
00:33:41,436 --> 00:33:43,436
That’s why he acts like a jerk sometimes.

571
00:33:44,088 --> 00:33:45,745
He wasn’t like this before.

572
00:33:47,431 --> 00:33:48,305
How was he then?

573
00:33:52,501 --> 00:33:55,285
He used to be a workaholic.

574
00:33:55,490 --> 00:33:56,739
So hard-working.

575
00:33:57,541 --> 00:33:59,018
But because all he did was work,

576
00:33:59,737 --> 00:34:03,223
he got dumped without warning by his girlfriend of 7 years.

577
00:34:10,446 --> 00:34:13,752
After his heartbreak recovery, he was back again.

578
00:34:15,029 --> 00:34:16,340
He pretended to forget his past.

579
00:34:16,340 --> 00:34:20,964
He became a drinker, a player who wasn’t serious with anyone just to torture himself.

580
00:34:22,362 --> 00:34:24,362
At one point, I thought he had moved on.

581
00:34:25,179 --> 00:34:28,991
He even insisted on going to his ex’s wedding.

582
00:34:29,696 --> 00:34:30,659
You know how it turned out?

583
00:34:30,871 --> 00:34:31,467
Bad.

584
00:34:34,625 --> 00:34:37,702
JJ and I drank with him a lot.

585
00:34:38,115 --> 00:34:40,700
Without knowing it, we were in a car he was driving.

586
00:34:41,593 --> 00:34:44,442
We would have got to the condo safely

587
00:34:46,140 --> 00:34:48,540
if that car hadn’t cut him off.

588
00:34:53,178 --> 00:34:55,717
Kuafah’s car hit the side of the road.

589
00:34:56,249 --> 00:34:57,792
Luckily, no one was injured.

590
00:34:58,217 --> 00:35:00,021
The police had him tested for alcohol.

591
00:35:00,980 --> 00:35:03,780
As punishment, the court ordered that we all do community service.

592
00:35:04,532 --> 00:35:08,622
Actually, his dad could help soften the sentence.

593
00:35:09,426 --> 00:35:11,018
But he wanted to teach him a lesson.

594
00:35:11,702 --> 00:35:13,555
And that’s why we are here.

595
00:35:16,862 --> 00:35:19,319
It’s true we’re here because we did something bad.

596
00:35:19,922 --> 00:35:24,061
But my friend isn’t here just to change a place to drink as you said.

597
00:35:25,295 --> 00:35:27,753
He went out because he had other reasons.

598
00:35:41,650 --> 00:35:42,997
Does it hurt, good girl?

599
00:35:43,481 --> 00:35:46,526
- No. It doesn’t hurt at all.
- Actually, he didn’t go out to buy drinks.

600
00:35:47,300 --> 00:35:50,133
He went to buy more medicines and supplies for the health center.

601
00:35:50,133 --> 00:35:51,364
I’m going to apply a plaster now.

602
00:35:52,669 --> 00:35:56,122
I got you a piggy plaster here. You like it?

603
00:35:56,122 --> 00:35:57,191
Really?

604
00:35:58,041 --> 00:36:00,041
Supplies at the health center are too old.

605
00:36:00,766 --> 00:36:02,244
Some medicines have expired.

606
00:36:05,944 --> 00:36:09,540
Dr. Fah is sorry for coming back so late.

607
00:36:10,101 --> 00:36:11,219
Will you forgive me?

608
00:36:11,546 --> 00:36:12,428
I will.

609
00:36:13,028 --> 00:36:14,522
But he also came back with liquor.

610
00:36:15,093 --> 00:36:16,277
That’s why it looked quite bad.

611
00:36:33,172 --> 00:36:33,779
Hi,

612
00:36:34,367 --> 00:36:35,042
Teacher.

613
00:36:44,411 --> 00:36:45,856
Can I borrow your phone?

614
00:36:45,856 --> 00:36:47,178
I will try to call home.

615
00:36:47,178 --> 00:36:49,178
In case they can find me a new volunteer location.

616
00:36:49,220 --> 00:36:53,081
Your dad said if you couldn’t handle it,

617
00:36:53,323 --> 00:36:54,703
you could come back to Bangkok.

618
00:36:55,127 --> 00:36:56,057
So…

619
00:36:56,906 --> 00:36:57,823
When are you leaving?

620
00:36:58,264 --> 00:36:59,347
Tomorrow morning.

621
00:36:59,660 --> 00:37:01,121
Did you talk to Prince last night?

622
00:37:01,811 --> 00:37:02,433
Why?

623
00:37:02,433 --> 00:37:03,580
Follow us and you’ll see.

624
00:37:04,037 --> 00:37:04,911
What is happening here?

625
00:37:36,004 --> 00:37:36,674
So…

626
00:37:39,595 --> 00:37:40,752
Do you

627
00:37:41,563 --> 00:37:42,717
have anything to say?

628
00:37:50,679 --> 00:37:51,588
Your bag.

629
00:37:52,455 --> 00:37:53,905
A prince crown bag.

630
00:37:55,008 --> 00:37:55,868
Did you make it yourself?

631
00:37:56,439 --> 00:37:58,382
The children made it for me in art class.

632
00:37:59,027 --> 00:38:01,365
I taught them what Prince meant.

633
00:38:02,364 --> 00:38:03,707
And they made me this.

634
00:38:07,089 --> 00:38:07,894
Cute.

635
00:38:08,535 --> 00:38:09,176
Right?

636
00:38:09,912 --> 00:38:11,136
I fell for it the moment I saw it.

637
00:38:11,475 --> 00:38:12,715
I meant you.

638
00:38:13,706 --> 00:38:17,228
You must be very cute in their eyes. That’s why they made it for you.

639
00:38:17,932 --> 00:38:19,171
What are you saying?

640
00:38:22,313 --> 00:38:23,933
Here. Take it.

641
00:38:29,954 --> 00:38:30,827
A dinner box.

642
00:38:34,251 --> 00:38:35,378
I made it.

643
00:38:36,082 --> 00:38:37,786
It might not be as good as the food in Bangkok.

644
00:38:38,017 --> 00:38:40,315
But it’s not spicy. I think you can handle it.

645
00:38:43,315 --> 00:38:44,258
Thank you.

646
00:38:45,671 --> 00:38:47,671
Such a nice farewell dinner.

647
00:38:52,136 --> 00:38:53,042
So…

648
00:38:54,501 --> 00:38:55,595
When are you leaving?

649
00:38:58,872 --> 00:39:00,196
Tomorrow morning.

650
00:39:02,074 --> 00:39:03,334
Don’t need to shoo me away now.

651
00:39:04,595 --> 00:39:06,172
I won’t bother you for long.

652
00:39:09,455 --> 00:39:10,251
Well then.

653
00:39:14,225 --> 00:39:15,429
May I get inside?

654
00:39:24,931 --> 00:39:26,044
Thank you.

655
00:39:39,164 --> 00:39:41,840
Mesa, can I borrow your phone?

656
00:39:45,584 --> 00:39:47,584
When will you leave my phone alone?

657
00:39:47,584 --> 00:39:49,394
I told you there’s no phone reception.

658
00:39:49,636 --> 00:39:50,718
Why do you still want it?

659
00:39:50,718 --> 00:39:51,636
Whatever.

660
00:39:51,748 --> 00:39:53,241
I will try to call home.

661
00:39:53,241 --> 00:39:55,315
In case they can find me a new volunteer location.

662
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:03,732
What?

663
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:08,276
I told Teacher Prince you went to the city to buy medicines.

664
00:40:08,528 --> 00:40:09,966
He hasn’t forgiven you?

665
00:40:11,065 --> 00:40:12,475
I guess he has.

666
00:40:12,475 --> 00:40:14,137
But what am I supposed to do?

667
00:40:14,361 --> 00:40:20,235
You want me to tell him, “Oh! I changed my mind.”

668
00:40:20,381 --> 00:40:21,397
“I’m not leaving anymore.”

669
00:40:21,397 --> 00:40:22,254
Like that?

670
00:40:22,381 --> 00:40:23,377
That isn’t cool.

671
00:40:23,715 --> 00:40:24,497
Cool?

672
00:40:24,497 --> 00:40:25,828
When did you say you’re leaving?

673
00:40:26,062 --> 00:40:26,972
Tomorrow morning.

674
00:40:29,213 --> 00:40:29,965
Wait a minute.

675
00:40:30,291 --> 00:40:31,170
Tomorrow morning?

676
00:40:31,170 --> 00:40:31,763
Yeah.

677
00:40:32,351 --> 00:40:34,595
We haven’t even done unpacking yet,

678
00:40:34,756 --> 00:40:35,835
Mr. cool guy!

679
00:40:35,835 --> 00:40:39,895
What? You want to leave right after you just came?

680
00:40:39,895 --> 00:40:41,554
Stop complaining.

681
00:40:41,554 --> 00:40:43,252
Don’t you want to get out of here asap?

682
00:40:43,516 --> 00:40:44,861
Give me your phone.

683
00:40:44,965 --> 00:40:46,084
I’ll try to call home.

684
00:40:46,500 --> 00:40:47,614
Here.

685
00:40:47,614 --> 00:40:48,428
Take it.

686
00:40:48,795 --> 00:40:50,372
Good luck with the reception.

687
00:40:52,790 --> 00:40:53,812
Is this one yours?

688
00:40:54,023 --> 00:40:55,720
Yes. I just told you to grab it.

689
00:41:01,979 --> 00:41:03,429
Come on, reception.

690
00:41:03,850 --> 00:41:05,681
Give me something here.

691
00:41:27,467 --> 00:41:28,368
Hello, Dao.

692
00:41:28,368 --> 00:41:29,467
It’s me, Fah.

693
00:41:29,839 --> 00:41:32,452
I borrowed Mesa’s phone.

694
00:41:32,934 --> 00:41:34,934
I thought you forgot about your brother.

695
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:36,297
(Sorry.)

696
00:41:36,741 --> 00:41:38,372
There’s no phone signal up here.

697
00:41:38,809 --> 00:41:41,485
I had to walk all over the mountain to get a signal.

698
00:41:42,784 --> 00:41:44,595
How are you doing anyway?

699
00:41:45,528 --> 00:41:46,955
(Not so good.)

700
00:41:46,955 --> 00:41:48,046
That’s why I called.

701
00:41:49,170 --> 00:41:52,016
I’ve got a favor to ask.

702
00:41:52,650 --> 00:41:55,939
Can you find me a new volunteer location?

703
00:41:55,939 --> 00:41:56,994
Somewhere not here.

704
00:41:58,426 --> 00:42:00,722
I knew you’d call asking for this.

705
00:42:00,722 --> 00:42:01,609
Actually,

706
00:42:01,905 --> 00:42:06,337
your dad said if you couldn’t handle it,

707
00:42:06,460 --> 00:42:07,844
you could come back for the community service in Bangkok.

708
00:42:08,140 --> 00:42:08,925
Seriously?

709
00:42:09,595 --> 00:42:10,406
What service?

710
00:42:10,786 --> 00:42:13,412
Cleaning the city intersections. Want that?

711
00:42:15,252 --> 00:42:16,108
No.

712
00:42:16,108 --> 00:42:19,239
Is there anything medical-related?

713
00:42:19,392 --> 00:42:20,248
No?

714
00:42:23,229 --> 00:42:25,409
Dao, I gotta go.

715
00:42:25,675 --> 00:42:27,210
I guess I’m being too loud.

716
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:28,875
People might come yelling at me.

717
00:42:29,595 --> 00:42:31,426
I’ll call you again when I go to Chiang Mai downtown.

718
00:42:31,426 --> 00:42:32,472
Talk to you later.

719
00:42:50,006 --> 00:42:50,665
What?

720
00:42:51,468 --> 00:42:53,633
You two haven’t packed?

721
00:42:53,633 --> 00:42:54,451
Fah.

722
00:42:54,741 --> 00:42:56,186
Did you talk to Prince last night?

723
00:42:56,741 --> 00:42:59,854
No. Why?

724
00:43:00,310 --> 00:43:01,676
Follow us and you’ll see.

725
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:04,795
Move. Why just standing there?

726
00:43:26,179 --> 00:43:27,105
What is happening here?

727
00:43:28,373 --> 00:43:31,688
Teacher Prince and the kids have been cleaning since dawn.

728
00:43:33,385 --> 00:43:35,533
Did you tell him we’re not leaving?

729
00:43:40,899 --> 00:43:42,434
It’s dusty here.

730
00:43:42,961 --> 00:43:44,750
So I wanted to help you clean it up.

731
00:43:45,171 --> 00:43:47,171
Right. We’re doing our best.

732
00:43:47,171 --> 00:43:48,304
Do you like it, Dr. Fah?

733
00:43:49,495 --> 00:43:50,819
Uh…

734
00:43:51,908 --> 00:43:53,422
The kids are helping here.

735
00:43:53,612 --> 00:43:54,359
Don't you like that?

736
00:43:57,991 --> 00:43:58,895
I do.

737
00:43:59,402 --> 00:44:00,244
Of course.

738
00:44:00,669 --> 00:44:01,675
Thank you.

739
00:44:05,489 --> 00:44:08,863
Dr. Fah, my plaster is about to come off.

740
00:44:09,155 --> 00:44:12,444
Because you’re helping me clean?

741
00:44:12,529 --> 00:44:13,144
Yes.

742
00:44:13,841 --> 00:44:17,363
Then I'll apply you a new one.

743
00:44:17,644 --> 00:44:18,210
Okay.

744
00:44:18,210 --> 00:44:20,115
Do you like a kitty plaster?

745
00:44:20,115 --> 00:44:21,235
I do.

746
00:44:30,328 --> 00:44:31,926
From what I see,

747
00:44:32,309 --> 00:44:34,985
we don’t need to hurry home anymore.

748
00:44:37,600 --> 00:44:38,670
I see something too.

749
00:44:38,670 --> 00:44:39,211
Okay.

750
00:44:39,317 --> 00:44:41,035
Let me apply a new plaster for you.

751
00:44:41,500 --> 00:44:42,296
See what?

752
00:44:43,222 --> 00:44:45,285
I see we’ll be here for a long time.

753
00:44:49,083 --> 00:44:50,392
Okay.

754
00:44:50,515 --> 00:44:51,544
And we’re done.

755
00:44:51,801 --> 00:44:53,674
Thank you, Dr. Fah.

756
00:45:06,288 --> 00:45:09,239
I won’t tell the village chief about the other day.

757
00:45:10,652 --> 00:45:12,652
But if you do something terrible again,

758
00:45:13,472 --> 00:45:14,859
you won’t get away with it.

759
00:45:18,218 --> 00:45:21,233
Keep a close eye on my then, Teacher.

760
00:45:23,997 --> 00:45:25,743
Please take care of me.

761
00:45:37,115 --> 00:45:41,630
Everything about love, in my viewpoint, is chaotic.

762
00:45:42,974 --> 00:45:44,847
Directed by Siwaj Sawatmaneekul

763
00:46:04,852 --> 00:46:05,512
Hey!

764
00:46:05,787 --> 00:46:06,958
How did you get in here?

765
00:46:06,958 --> 00:46:08,783
Don’t you have to conduct medical check-ups today?

766
00:46:08,783 --> 00:46:10,541
I’m feeling hot.

767
00:46:10,541 --> 00:46:12,219
If you don’t believe me, feel it.

768
00:46:12,219 --> 00:46:13,252
I like Teacher Prince.

769
00:46:13,401 --> 00:46:15,401
Can you spy on him and see if he’s dating someone?

770
00:46:16,182 --> 00:46:17,057
Shit!

771
00:46:17,057 --> 00:46:18,182
I just stepped on pigshit.

772
00:46:19,059 --> 00:46:20,890
Are you nuts? Why does it have to be me?

773
00:46:20,890 --> 00:46:21,522
Wait.

774
00:46:21,675 --> 00:46:22,626
What are you doing?

775
00:46:22,715 --> 00:46:25,096
Other people get generic check-ups.

776
00:46:25,218 --> 00:46:27,514
But you get a special checkup.

